Ursa Major's newest additive manufacturing facility, located in Boardman Ohio, is the evolution of the advanced
manufacturing technologies employed to build Ursa Major's high-end solid rocket motor capabilities. Originally
part of the Youngstown Business Incubator (YBI), Ursa recently moved into a YBI-funded warehouse to allow
for additional machinery. In alignment with Governor DeWine's proclamation to mature a thriving additive
manufacturing ecosystem in Youngstown, Ohio, Ursa Major is interested in further expansion and committed to
developing the community workforce and tradecraft necessary to make the Governor's vision a reality through
partnerships and initiatives such as America
Makes and Jobs Ohio.

