A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Develop a long-term Soldier/Squad as a System integration platform in connection with the Close Combat Integration Enterprise (CCIE) to ensure interoperability as part
of the integrated Joint Forces. Verify and develop prototype digital engineering tools that provide Systems Engineering, Configuration Management, and Evaluation in
a virtual and physical environment. Using enhancements to the Adaptive Squad Architecture (ASA) digital tools verify development of interface controls documents, and
connection points to support the rapid integration of the CCIE programs with all other dismounted Soldier equipment. Prototype capabilities for evaluation and integration
include new measurements and methodologies from S&T programs and future requirements. Funding for this program aligns with the Army's priorities in support of
Digital Engineering and Transformation and is a Soldier Lethality Cross Functional Team priority.

