A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Surface Navy Integrated Undersea Tactical Technology (SNIUTT) is a software tool which provides contact recognition training modules for Mine Countermeasures
(MCM) sensor systems. SNIUTT training modules include skills and refresher/proficiency training; the contact recognition training focuses on detection, classification,
and identification of mine-like contacts. The modules run on existing PMA and training systems; this implementation reinforces PMA procedures for Fleet operators.
Modules are customized based on Fleet-user needs for a specific weapons system and are used both in the classroom and at the squadrons, as contact recognition
is a perishable skill. SNIUTT training modules are available for the following systems: 1) Post Mission Analysis training systems for AN/AQS-24; 2) Net-Centric Sensor
Analysis for Mine Warfare (NSAM) Post Mission Analysis training systems for AN/AQS-20C; 3) Net-Centric Sensor Analysis for Mine Warfare (NSAM) for ALMDS.

